ich we hired additional employees and also accounted for within our financial projections. Numerous weeks after the award, the client decided to withdraw 10 of the projects. This decision left us with just 3 projects in addition to a surplus of employees that we would have to reallocate in addition to significant financial implications.</span></p>','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(41,'App\\Study',9,1,'solution','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">We responded to the issue by reallocating the staff to other assignments in different roles that were within their skill sets for the time being. Our business cycle, business development efforts, growth, and backlog indicated that the projects we had lost would soon be replaced with projects from new clients. With these new opportunities, we would be able to continue our normal operations.</span></p>','<p><span class=\"s1\">We responded to the issue by reallocating the staff to other assignments in different roles that were within their skill sets for the time being. Our business cycle, business development efforts, growth, and backlog indicated that the projects we had lost would soon be replaced with projects from new clients. With these new opportunities, we would be able to continue our normal operations.</span></p>','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(42,'App\\Study',9,1,'analysis','<p>n/a</p>','','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(43,'App\\Study',9,1,'excerpt','&nbsp;\r\nThe company for which I work for was awarded 13 projects for which we hired additional employees and also accounted for within our financial projections. Numerous weeks after the award, the client decided to withdraw 10 of the projects. This decision left us with just 3 projects in addition to a surplus of employees that we would have to reallocate in addition to significant financial implications....','The company for which I work for was awarded 13 projects for which we hired additional employees and also accounted for within our financial projections. Numerous weeks after the award, the client decided to withdraw 10 of the projects. This decision left us with just 3 projects in addition to a surplus of employees that we would have to reallocate in addition to significant financial implications....','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(44,'App\\Study',9,1,'delivery_method',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(45,'App\\Study',9,1,'estimated_schedule',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(46,'App\\Study',9,1,'contract_value',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(47,'App\\Study',9,1,'market_sector',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(48,'App\\Study',9,1,'topic',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(49,'App\\Study',9,1,'location',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:15','2016-04-11 16:44:15'),(50,'App\\Study',8,1,'problem','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">A project we were working on involved the erection of a 5-story precast garage on top of a cast-in-place foundation. About 3 stories into the erection, we noticed some cracks one of the foundation piers in the center of the garage. Upon investigation of the pier, it was determined that several stirrups were located in the wrong place. The project was already delayed due to a tough winter and had to be completed on time so as to avoid incurring any penalties.</span></p>','<p><span class=\"s1\">A project we were working on involved the erection of a 5-story precast garage on top of a cast-in-place foundation. About 3 stories into the erection, we noticed some cracks one of the foundation piers in the center of the garage. Upon investigation of the pier, it was determined that several stirrups were located in the wrong place. The project was already delayed due to a tough winter and had to be completed on time so as to avoid incurring any penalties.</span></p>','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(51,'App\\Study',8,1,'solution','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">In order to avoid delaying the project while the problem was addressed, we worked with a reshore designer, precast designer, and the original structural engineer to design a system to shore the building while continuing the precast erection and the removal and replacement of the missing rebar stirrups. An additional work crew was required to remove and replace the pier without delaying the original construction team beyond the investigation delay and in due course, meet the project&rsquo;s deadline.</span></p>','<p><span class=\"s1\">In order to avoid delaying the project while the problem was addressed, we worked with a reshore designer, precast designer, and the original structural engineer to design a system to shore the building while continuing the precast erection and the removal and replacement of the missing rebar stirrups. An additional work crew was required to remove and replace the pier without delaying the original construction team beyond the investigation delay and in due course, meet the project&rsquo;s deadline.</span></p>','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(52,'App\\Study',8,1,'analysis','<p>&nbsp;n/a</p>','','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(53,'App\\Study',8,1,'excerpt','&nbsp;\r\nA project we were working on involved the erection of a 5-story precast garage on top of a cast-in-place foundation. About 3 stories into the erection, we noticed some cracks one of the foundation piers in the center of the garage. Upon investigation of the pier, it was determined that several stirrups were located in the wrong place. The project was already delayed due to a tough winter and had to be completed on time so as to avoid incurring any penalties....','A project we were working on involved the erection of a 5-story precast garage on top of a cast-in-place foundation. About 3 stories into the erection, we noticed some cracks one of the foundation piers in the center of the garage. Upon investigation of the pier, it was determined that several stirrups were located in the wrong place. The project was already delayed due to a tough winter and had to be completed on time so as to avoid incurring any penalties....','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(54,'App\\Study',8,1,'delivery_method',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(55,'App\\Study',8,1,'estimated_schedule',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(56,'App\\Study',8,1,'contract_value',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(57,'App\\Study',8,1,'market_sector',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(58,'App\\Study',8,1,'topic',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(59,'App\\Study',8,1,'location',NULL,'','2016-04-11 16:44:32','2016-04-11 16:44:32'),(60,'App\\Study',7,1,'problem','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">On a recent high-rise, class &lsquo;A&rsquo;, office tower, the controls subcontractor was awarded a contract that included the integration of the building\'s fire alarm control panel and the respective life-safety systems. Due to recent code changes and the fact that the fire alarm system was a newer generation; the system required more detailed controls. As a result, many questions and concerns arose.</span></p>','<p>On a recent high-rise, class &lsquo;A&rsquo;, office tower, the controls subcontractor was awarded a contract that included the integration of the building\'s fire alarm control panel and the respective life-safety systems. Due to recent code changes and the fact that the fire alarm system was a newer generation; the system required more detailed controls. As a result, many questions and concerns arose.</p>','2016-04-11 16:44:50','2016-04-11 16:44:50'),(61,'App\\Study',7,1,'solution','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The complete system was studied and eventually broken down in order to revise the scope. Once broke down, the controls 